SUMMARY:Lunch & Learn: Building a Brand from Scratch
DESCRIPTION:Ever wondered how a product actually comes to life? After lea
 ving a cutting-edge career at Twitter and Google to build something of he
 r own\, Erica Anderson is now co-founder &amp\; CEO of The New Savant\, a
 n indie fragrance company. Erica will walk through what it takes to turn 
 an idea into something tangible. From early concepts to branding and laun
 ch\, this session offers a behind-the-scenes look at creative entrepreneu
 rship and what it really takes to get something off the ground.Erica Ande
 rson\,  Co-founder &amp\; CEO\, The New SavantB.A. '06\, JournalismErica 
 Anderson has spent more than 15 years operating at the intersection of me
 dia\, technology\, and consumer brands—driving impact inside some of th
 e world's most influential companies\, including Twitter\, Google\, CBS N
 ews\, MTV News\, and Vox Media. A few of Anderson's notable accomplishmen
 ts include being employee #300 at Twitter\, where they worked on a global
  effort to integrate Twitter into newsrooms\; working for Katie Couric at
  CBS Evening News\; and traveling the world for Google on a mission to co
 mbat misinformation.Now\, as a founder\, Anderson is in their fourth year
  bootstrapping The New Savant\, an indie fragrance brand\, which has foun
 d an immediate product market fit in a $44B global industry.This event wi
 ll take place in the Wells Conference Room on the first floor of Owen Hal
 l.This event is Momentum eligible.Accessibility accommodationsThe Walter 
 Center strives to host inclusive\, accessible events that enable all indi
 viduals to engage fully. To request an accommodation or for inquiries abo
 ut accessibility\, please use ourEvent Accommodations Request Formor cont
 act ourevent accessibility coordinator.
