 itated scholar in communication studies whose research focuses on communi
 cation history\, including (post-)socialist transformation and memory stu
 dies\, as well as public sphere and media change\, with a further focus o
 n international communication. She has conducted research on topics such 
 as journalistic practices\, media use\, and digital literacy in Sub-Sahar
 an Africa and the Middle East. Her work integrates qualitative and quanti
 tative methods within comparative research designs\, frequently carried o
 ut in the context of European collaborative projects. Her current researc
 h examines the interplay between media and social inequality in post-indu
 strial contexts in Eastern Germany and Northern England.</p><p>  To join 
 the keynote session online\, please register here: <a href="https://iu.zo
 om.us/meeting/register/i6jkRgUsQHuVGCs1wPAabg">https://iu.zoom.us/meeting
