LOCATION:IU CINEMA
GEO:39.168613;-86.517376
SUMMARY:When Everyone Swims (Jerald Harkness\, 2025) Screening and Q & A 
 w/Jerald Harkness
DESCRIPTION:Directed by IU alum and BFCA Advisory Board Member Jerald Har
 kness\, When Everyone Swims (2025) is a documentary that chronicles the U
 .S.'s tenuous relationship with swimming\, the importance of learning to 
 swim and water safety\, and advocates for everyone to have access to pool
 s and safe places to participate in water sports. Visit https://whenevery
 oneswims.org/ (https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%
 3A%2F%2Findiana.us17.list-manage.com%2Ftrack%2Fclick%3Fu%3Df603b0d14ab605
 9bea01fbc72%26id%3Deec815c828%26e%3Daae39a2b17&amp\;data=05%7C02%7Cbfca%4
 0iu.edu%7C869b1c5fe80a418f8bd308de55221b8c%7C1113be34aed14d00ab4bcdd02510
 be91%7C1%7C0%7C639041802152870142%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGk
 iOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3
 D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&amp\;sdata=vFI61%2Fso6eeqcTGNhsNVMIrIi1JMa8qf1hl8XlyIcL
 s%3D&amp\;reserved=0) to view the trailer and join the movement.  This pr
 ogram is a partnership between the School of Public Health\, IU Cinema\, 
 and the Black Film Center &amp\; Archive.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p data-olk-copy-source="MessageBody">  Dire
 cted by IU alum and BFCA Advisory Board Member Jerald Harkness\, <em>When
  Everyone Swims</em> (2025) is a documentary that chronicles the U.S.'s t
 enuous relationship with swimming\, the importance of learning to swim an
 d water safety\, and advocates for everyone to have access to pools and s
 afe places to participate in water sports. Visit <a title="Original URL: 
 https://indiana.us17.list-manage.com/track/click?u=f603b0d14ab6059bea01fb
 c72&amp\;id=eec815c828&amp\;e=aae39a2b17. Click or tap if you trust this 
 link." href="https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A
 %2F%2Findiana.us17.list-manage.com%2Ftrack%2Fclick%3Fu%3Df603b0d14ab6059b
 ea01fbc72%26id%3Deec815c828%26e%3Daae39a2b17&amp\;data=05%7C02%7Cbfca%40i
