BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:IU Media School
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260501
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260502
LOCATION:Black Film Center and Archive\, 1320 E. 10th Street\, Wells Libr
 ary 044\, Bloomington\, IN\, 47405 - Room Number: Phyllis Klotman Classro
 om 044B
GEO:39.171255;-86.516556
SUMMARY:Rising from the Dust: The Legacy of Michelle Materre exhibit
DESCRIPTION:Curated by archivists Sarah Petras and Dan Hassoun\, this exh
 ibit showcases posters\, collages\, photos\, and realia relating to the c
 areer of pioneering film distributor Michelle Materre\, including origina
 l materials from the first release of Daughters of the Dust! Stop by the 
 BFCA office to get a look at this exhibit\, which will stay up for the re
 mainder of the 2025-2026 academic year.&#160\;
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Curated by archivists Sarah Petras and 
 Dan Hassoun\, this exhibit showcases posters\, collages\, photos\, and re
 alia relating to the career of pioneering film distributor Michelle Mater
 re\, including original materials from the first release of <em>Daughters
  of the Dust</em>! Stop by the BFCA office to get a look at this exhibit\
 , which will stay up for the remainder of the 2025-2026 academic year.&#1
 60\;</p>
